   <S PAR='1' RSNT='1' SNO='1'>CHAPTER SIX THE BODY OF CHRIST Scripture Reading: Eph 1:23 OUTLINE It is the intrinsic significance of the church.</S>
   <S PAR='2' RSNT='1' SNO='2'>It is the divine constitution of the Triune God with the believers in Christ Eph 4:4-6.</S>
   <S PAR='3' RSNT='1' SNO='3'>It is a mingling of divinity with humanity.</S>
   <S PAR='4' RSNT='1' SNO='4'>It is an organism, both divine and human, to express Christ.</S>
   <S PAR='5' RSNT='1' SNO='5'>It is the fullness of the all-inclusive Christ, the One who fills all in all Eph 1:23: Fullness is the issue of the riches of Christ Eph 3:8.</S>
   <S PAR='6' RSNT='1' SNO='6'>Fullness is the expression of the inner riches.</S>
   <S PAR='7' RSNT='1' SNO='7'>Such an organic Body is: Undivided and indivisible as Christ is 1 Cor 1:13a.</S>
   <S PAR='8' RSNT='1' SNO='8'>Not autonomous.</S>
   <S PAR='9' RSNT='1' SNO='9'>This unique Body of Christ is expressed in many local churches Rev 1:11: In the divine oneness as it is with the Triune God John 17:11, 21, 23.</S>
   <S PAR='10' RSNT='1' SNO='10'>In the divine nature, element, essence, expression, function, and testimony.</S>
   <S PAR='11' RSNT='1' SNO='11'>Kept by the believers in the practical one accord Acts 1:14; 2:46; 4:24; 5:12; 15:25; Rom 15:6.</S>
   <S PAR='12' RSNT='1' SNO='12'>The divine oneness of the Body of Christ should be kept both in the local churches as the local expressions of the Body and in the universal source and substance.</S>
   <S PAR='13' RSNT='1' SNO='13'>This genuine oneness of the Body of Christ is one crucial point of the Lord's recovery in the consummating age.</S>
   <S PAR='14' RSNT='1' SNO='14'>All the problems of the church today are due to the ignorance concerning the Body of Christ.</S>
   </TEXT>
